How to Run the Application
--------------------------
1)Start the Backend:
Navigate to the backend folder and run:

       node server.js

Ensure your MongoDB instance is running.

2)View the Frontend:
Open the index.html file in your web browser. You can use an extension like Live Server for VS Code to serve the static files easily. 

You now have a functional web application where the AngularJS frontend sends data to and receives data from the Express.js backend. 
